  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, roasted chana from the office canteen — does it have that perfect crunchy bite?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, not sure about that. I usually eat sabzi and roti for lunch. But sometimes yes, roasted chana is okay. Why? Did you try it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Fair enough — sometimes simple is best. I’m curious, what’s your favourite kind of sabzi for lunch?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Aloo gobhi sabzi is my usual go-to. It's simple, tasty, and not too heavy. But hey, I do get bored of it sometimes. What about you — any sabzi you love?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Aloo gobhi is a classic — you really can’t go wrong with it. I like simple dishes too, but I’m not a big sabzi person. I prefer dal and rice. What’s your take on dal?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Dal is good, but I often skip it because it feels too heavy for me. Maybe I should try it more often. I like moong dal better than other types."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — some days you just want something lighter. Moong dal is a smart choice, it’s easier on the stomach. Have you tried making it with veggies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I have. Sometimes I add spinach or peas. Tastes better than plain dal, I think. But I get lazy and just eat it plain. You know how it is. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — lazy days happen, and plain dal is always there for you. Next time, maybe toss in some chopped tomatoes? It adds a nice kick. What do you think?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, tomatoes with dal? Never thought of that. Sounds good though. I’ll give it a try next time. Thanks for the idea! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome — small tweaks can make a big difference. Let me know how it turns out. I’d love to hear! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I will try it tomorrow. If not, maybe day after. You know, tomorrow is a busy day with a team meeting. I hope I stay awake. 😂"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds like a plan — take your time. Team meetings can be tough! What’s on the agenda? Work updates?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Just a usual one — we have to discuss a new feature for our app. Not too exciting, but necessary. Honestly, I’m still half-asleep. 😴"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right — new features are always a bit of a grind. Half-asleep or not, you’ll get through it. Coffee helping at all?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "A bit, but it’s not doing much. Maybe I’ll switch to tea. I have a bad feeling this meeting will drag on. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Tea can be a great switch — it’s gentler but still wakes you up. Here’s hoping the meeting moves quickly. Let me know how it goes!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks, I’ll switch to tea. Gotta get going now — meeting in an hour. Talk to you later, okay? 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Sure thing — good luck with the meeting, and take care! Talk to you soon!"
    }
  ],
